.TH "ee" "1" "2026-04-16"
.PP
.SH NAME
.PP
ee - easy editor
ree - restricted easy editor
.PP
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\fBee\fR [\fB-e\fR] [\fB-i\fR] [\fB-h\fR] [\fB+#\fR] [\fBfile\fR .\&.\&.\&]
\fBree\fR [\fB-e\fR] [\fB-i\fR] [\fB-h\fR] [\fB+#\fR] [\fBfile\fR .\&.\&.\&]
.PP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
The \fBee\fR editor is a simple, screen-oriented text editor designed to be
intuitive and easy to use.\& It is modeless, meaning it is always in text
insertion mode unless a prompt or menu is active.\&
.PP
\fBree\fR is a restricted version of \fBee\fR.\& It prevents the user from saving files
with names other than those specified on the command line, and disables shell
escapes.\&
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
\fB-e\fR
.RS 4
Disable expansion of tabs to spaces.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-i\fR
.RS 4
Disable the information window at the top of the screen.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB-h\fR
.RS 4
Disable border highlighting.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB+#\fR
.RS 4
Start the editor with the cursor at line number \fB#\fR.\&
.PP
.RE
.SH KEY BINDINGS
.PP
\fBee\fR uses control keys and function keys for navigation and commands.\&
.PP
.SS Basic Navigation
.PP
\fB\(haP\fR (Prev Page), \fB\(haN\fR (Next Page)
.RS 4
Move up or down one page.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBUp\fR, \fBDown\fR, \fBLeft\fR, \fBRight\fR (Arrow keys)
.RS 4
Move the cursor in the corresponding direction.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haO\fR
.RS 4
Move to end of line.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haD\fR
.RS 4
Move to beginning of line.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haT\fR
.RS 4
Move to top of text.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haB\fR
.RS 4
Move to bottom of text.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haY\fR (Adv Word)
.RS 4
Move to the next word.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haG \(haY\fR (Prev Word)
.RS 4
Move to the previous word.\&
.PP
.RE
.SS Editing
.PP
\fB\(haK\fR (Del Char)
.RS 4
Delete the character at the cursor.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBBackspace\fR
.RS 4
Delete the character before the cursor.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haL\fR (Del Line)
.RS 4
Delete the current line.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haW\fR (Del Word)
.RS 4
Delete the current word.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haU\fR (Mark)
.RS 4
Set a mark at the current cursor position.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haC\fR (Copy)
.RS 4
Copy the region between the mark and cursor to the clipboard.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haX\fR (Cut)
.RS 4
Cut the region between the mark and cursor to the clipboard.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haV\fR (Paste)
.RS 4
Paste the clipboard content at the cursor.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haJ\fR (Return)
.RS 4
Insert a newline.\&
.PP
.RE
.SS Command and Menu
.PP
\fB\(haE\fR (Command)
.RS 4
Prompt for an editor command.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBEsc\fR (Menu)
.RS 4
Open the main menu.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haG\fR (GOLD)
.RS 4
Enter GOLD mode for secondary commands.\&
.PP
.RE
.SH GOLD MODE COMMANDS
.PP
After pressing \fB\(haG\fR, the following secondary commands are available:
.PP
\fBEsc\fR
.RS 4
Open the main menu (required if \fBEsc\fR alone is remapped).\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haP\fR (Prev Buff)
.RS 4
Switch to the previous file buffer.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haN\fR (Next Buff)
.RS 4
Switch to the next file buffer.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haV\fR (Forward)
.RS 4
Search forward for the last searched string.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haR\fR (Reverse)
.RS 4
Search backward for the last searched string.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haX\fR (Fmt Parag)
.RS 4
Format the current paragraph.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haK\fR (Und Char)
.RS 4
Undelete the last deleted character.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haL\fR (Und Line)
.RS 4
Undelete the last deleted line.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haW\fR (Und Word)
.RS 4
Undelete the last deleted word.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haZ\fR (Repl Prmpt)
.RS 4
Prompt for string replacement.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\(haB\fR (Append)
.RS 4
Append the selected region to the clipboard.\&
.PP
.RE
.SH COMMANDS
.PP
Commands are entered at the \fB\(haE\fR prompt:
.PP
\fBhelp\fR
.RS 4
Display help information.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBfile\fR [\fB\fRname\fB\fR]
.RS 4
Print the current file name or set a new one.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBread\fR \fB\fRfilename\fB\fR
.RS 4
Read a file into the buffer.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBwrite\fR [\fB\fRfilename\fB\fR]
.RS 4
Write the buffer to a file.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBline\fR
.RS 4
Print the current line number.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBsearch\fR [\fB\fRstring\fB\fR]
.RS 4
Search for a string.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBcase\fR, \fBnocase\fR
.RS 4
Toggle case-sensitive search.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBexpand\fR, \fBnoexpand\fR
.RS 4
Toggle tab expansion.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB!\&cmd\fR
.RS 4
Execute \fB\fRcmd\fB\fR in a shell.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB><!\&cmd\fR
.RS 4
Pipe the buffer to \fB\fRcmd\fB\fR and replace it with the output.\&
.PP
.RE
.SH CONFIGURATION
.PP
\fBee\fR reads configuration from the following files in order:
.PP
1.\& \fB/usr/share/misc/init.\&ee\fR (system-wide)
2.\& \fB$HOME/.\&init.\&ee\fR (user-specific)
3.\& \fB.\&init.\&ee\fR (directory-specific)
.PP
.SS Custom Key Bindings
.PP
User-definable bindings are supported via the following commands in the
configuration file:
.PP
\fBBIND\fR \fB\fRkey\fB\fR \fB\fRcommand\fB\fR
.RS 4
Bind a base control key (e.\&g.\&, \fBBIND \(haA top_of_txt\fR).\&
.PP
.RE
\fBGBIND\fR \fB\fRkey\fB\fR \fB\fRcommand\fB\fR
.RS 4
Bind a GOLD mode key.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBEBIND\fR \fB\fRkey\fB\fR \fB\fRcommand\fB\fR
.RS 4
Bind an Emacs mode key.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB\fRcommand\fB\fR must be one of the internal command names (e.\&g.\&, \fBright\fR, \fBleft\fR,
\fBup\fR, \fBdown\fR, \fBbol\fR, \fBeol\fR, \fBnext_page\fR, \fBprev_page\fR, \fBtop_of_txt\fR,
\fBbottom_of_txt\fR, \fBdel_char\fR, \fBdel_word\fR, \fBdel_line\fR, \fBund_char\fR, \fBund_word\fR,
\fBund_line\fR, \fBcopy\fR, \fBcut\fR, \fBpaste\fR, \fBappend\fR, \fBmark\fR, \fBsearch\fR,
\fBsearch_reverse\fR, \fBsearch_prompt\fR, \fBreplace_prompt\fR, \fBcommand_prompt\fR,
\fBgold_toggle\fR, \fBredraw\fR, \fBhelp\fR, \fBmenu\fR, \fBformat\fR, \fBadv_word\fR, \fBprev_word\fR,
\fBnewline\fR, \fBbackspace\fR).\&
.PP
